<subSubSection id="3B0E3643A46FBB70561B56A6F70FCC7D" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" type="taxon discussion">
<paragraph id="4E2D5FCA18D24279F093421AAAE6B675" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817">Taxon discussion</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B5D4E793907A343864C43DB969ECD91F" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817">
<taxonomicName id="692A0B967BF495A4B9EBEB780FF40479" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Jacobaea" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Jacobaea othonnae" order="Asterales" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="othonnae">
<emphasis id="F1F32C0E1D862D733D4350A6FB5D1C07" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817">Jacobaea othonnae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is rare in Greece, known from the floristic regions of North Pindos (NPi) and NE (
<bibRefCitation id="4A81001097A031659C66766F150879C1" author="Dimopoulos, P." journalOrPublisher="Botanischer Garten und Botanisches Museum Berlin-Dahlem, Berlin; Hellenic Botanical Society, Athens" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" refId="B7668013" refString="Dimopoulos, P., Raus, T., Bergmeier, E., Constantinidis, T., Iatrou, G., Kokkini, S., Strid, A., D.Tzanoudakis, , 2013. Vascular plants of Greece: An annotated checklist. Botanischer Garten und Botanisches Museum Berlin-Dahlem, Berlin; Hellenic Botanical Society, Athens" title="Vascular plants of Greece: An annotated checklist" year="2013">Dimopoulos et al. 2013</bibRefCitation>
). In North Pindos, specifically, there is only one record from Mt. Timfi (
<bibRefCitation id="59CA27F89A1720156708EA759A1D0011" author="Authier, P." journalOrPublisher="Phytologia Balcanica, 20 (1): 99 - 137" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" refId="B7667811" refString="Authier, P., 2014. New floristic records in the Balkans: 24. Phytologia Balcanica, 20 (1): 99-137" title="New floristic records in the Balkans: 24" year="2014">Authier 2014</bibRefCitation>
), while in the NE, there are records from Mt. Athos (
<bibRefCitation id="C072B116BB89959FE39F5419802B2192" author="Boissier, E." journalOrPublisher="H. George, Genevae et Basileae, Lugduni" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" refId="B7667877" refString="Boissier, E., 1875. Flora Orientalis sive enumeratio plantarum in oriente a Graecia et Aegypto ad Indiae fines hucusque observatarum 3. H. George, Genevae et Basileae, Lugduni" title="Flora Orientalis sive enumeratio plantarum in oriente a Graecia et Aegypto ad Indiae fines hucusque observatarum 3" year="1875">Boissier 1875</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="273D6902EB258C3703B6A8374182C1C4" author="Authier, P." journalOrPublisher="Phytologia Balcanica, 20 (1): 99 - 137" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" refId="B7667811" refString="Authier, P., 2014. New floristic records in the Balkans: 24. Phytologia Balcanica, 20 (1): 99-137" title="New floristic records in the Balkans: 24" year="2014">Authier 2014</bibRefCitation>
), Mt. Pangeo (a.n. 1983136, LD!) and Mt. Vrondous (
<bibRefCitation id="C13387326D70DB249A214C6B57D9DEB5" author="Authier, P." journalOrPublisher="Phytologia Balcanica, 20 (1): 99 - 137" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" refId="B7667811" refString="Authier, P., 2014. New floristic records in the Balkans: 24. Phytologia Balcanica, 20 (1): 99-137" title="New floristic records in the Balkans: 24" year="2014">Authier 2014</bibRefCitation>
). According to 
<bibRefCitation id="6D613694DA18556424589377C0C4829E" author="Sutory, K." journalOrPublisher="Phytotaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" pagination="61 - 68" refId="B7669545" refString="Sutory, K., 2021. Taxonomic and nomenclatural notes on Jacobaea othonnae (Asteraceae - Senecioneae - Senecioninae). Phytotaxa 510 (1): 61 - 68" title="Taxonomic and nomenclatural notes on Jacobaea othonnae (Asteraceae - Senecioneae - Senecioninae)" volume="510" year="2021">
<normalizedToken id="C50745358B0C736837FB0C17F98222F2" originalValue="Sutorý">Sutory</normalizedToken>
(2021)
</bibRefCitation>
, the Mt. Athos plants are somewhat isolated, have woolly-tomentose synflorescences and involucres and belong to the distinct and local subsp. 
<taxonomicName id="07B53E42E2A73DC93628D17E1AB24BE8" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Jacobaea" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Jacobaea othonnae subsp. anomala" order="Asterales" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="othonnae" subSpecies="anomala">Jacobaea othonnae anomala</taxonomicName>
(Sm.) 
<normalizedToken id="E0413722B1D289500148E1F67C8E21F3" originalValue="Sutorý">Sutory</normalizedToken>
. The rest of the north-eastern populations are attributed to the typical subsp. 
<taxonomicName id="E299B09795C83E1B408EB5FDA3964BFB" authority="othonnae" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Jacobaea" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Jacobaea othonnae subsp. othonnae" order="Asterales" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="othonnae" subSpecies="othonnae">Jacobaea othonnae othonnae</taxonomicName>
and have glabrous synflorescences and involucres. The plants of Mt. Achladovouno (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="23B5CD8B615E1C79E54AC856B26EF864" captionStart="Figure 8" captionStartId="F7677574" captionText="Figure 8. Jacobaea othonnae subsp. anomala from Mt. Achladovouno (photo: P. Doumas)." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.10.e81817.figure8" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/640534" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817">8</figureCitation>
) seem to break this distribution pattern, as they present woolly-tomentose synflorescences, particularly at young age and, therefore, fit subsp. 
<taxonomicName id="F92AC92F17FAA5E2931567D32E11BB1F" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Jacobaea" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Jacobaea othonnae subsp. anomala" order="Asterales" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="othonnae" subSpecies="anomala">Jacobaea othonnae anomala</taxonomicName>
. Our new collection adds a second mountain locality to subsp. 
<taxonomicName id="3D62F937A0F8E829F2BCD756A7931FE7" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Jacobaea" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Jacobaea othonnae subsp. anomala" order="Asterales" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="subSpecies" species="othonnae" subSpecies="anomala">Jacobaea othonnae anomala</taxonomicName>
and extends its distribution ca. 120 km to the north-east (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="28C2FAFAAFBBA23EB6725A9385813555" captionStart="Figure 7" captionStartId="F7677570" captionText="Figure 7. Distribution map of Centaurea marmorea, Jacobaea othonnae subsp. anomala, Hesperis matronalis subsp. matronalis and Saponaria stranjensis in Greece." figureDoi="10.3897/BDJ.10.e81817.figure7" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/656686" pageId="0" pageNumber="81817">7</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
